title: ICE: fully private item in the table

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code needs debug assertions! ```Rust #![crate_type = "rlib"] #![cfg_attr(not(feature = "cargo-build"), feature(staged_api, core, no_std))] pub mod sysconf {} pub mod sysconf { pub static _SC_NPROCESSORS_ONLN: c_int = 84; } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` e69336efe035c274f2ee66922cd9cac6015956ea ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0428]: the name `sysconf` is defined multiple times --> 310b743961389e3451c10cc3fb8a2104bbaae065.rs:6:1 | 4 | pub mod sysconf {} | --------------- previous definition of the module `sysconf` here 5 | 6 | pub mod sysconf { | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ `sysconf` redefined here | = note: `sysconf` must be defined only once in the type namespace of this module error[E0412]: cannot find type `c_int` in this scope --> 310b743961389e3451c10cc3fb8a2104bbaae065.rs:7:38 | 7 | pub static _SC_NPROCESSORS_ONLN: c_int = 84; | ^^^^^ not found in this scope | help: consider importing one of these items | 7 | use std::ffi::c_int; | 7 | use std::os::raw::c_int; | ```
